Gerald turned away. There were one or two new pictures in the room, in the Futurist manner;
    there was a large piano. And these, with some ordinary London lodging-house furniture of the
    better sort, completed the whole.

“I wish she’d come to something different from national consciousness, then,” said Birkin;
    “especially as it only means a sort of commercial-industrial consciousness. I hate Italy and
    her national rant. And I think Barnes is an amateur.”

But now again she was under his domination; now, because she had dealt him this blow;
    because she had destroyed him, and she did not know how he had taken it. She watched him. He
    was interesting to her. She had lost her interest in Loerke.
